# Wellfit QA — Azure portal paths (STAGE)

Chris has Azure access. When guiding him, **name the exact left-nav item** from the App Service blade — do not invent alternate labels.

## Worldpay Wrapper STAGE

**App:** `stage-wf-worldpay-wrapper-api` (Web App)

### Left nav (as seen in portal)

| Section | Items Chris sees |
|---------|------------------|
| Top | Overview, Activity log, Access control (IAM), Tags, Diagnose and solve problems, Microsoft Defender for Cloud, Events, AI, Resource visualizer |
| **Deployment** | Deployment slots, Deployment Center |
| **Settings** | **Environment variables**, Configuration, Instances, Authentication, Identity, Backups, Custom domains, Certificates, Networking, WebJobs, Service Connector, Locks |
| Performance | Load Testing |
| App Service plan | App Service plan, Scale up, Scale out |
| Development Tools | SSH, Advanced Tools, Recommended services |
| API | API Management, API definition, CORS |
| **Monitoring** | Alerts, Metrics, **Logs**, Health check, **Application Insights**, Diagnostic settings, App Service logs, Log stream, Dashboards with Grafana |
| Automation | Tasks, Export template |
| Support | Resource health, Advisor recommendations |

### Where to look for what

| Need | Exact click path |
|------|------------------|
| App settings / flags / processor URL | **Settings → Environment variables** (not “Configuration” first — Chris’s UI lists Environment variables separately) |
| Feature flag eCheck | Env var `wellfit__featureFlags__WorldpayWrapper__ECheckEnabled` |
| Vantiv Pre-Live URL | Env var `processor__vantiv__url` → expected `https://payments.vantivprelive.com/vap/communicator/online` |
| Merchant id (Postman `accountId`) | Env var `processor__vantiv__merchantId` → `01264096` |
| Master submerchant (Azure only; **not** Postman subMerchantId) | `processor__vantiv__masterSubMerchantId` → `01291508` |
| Live request logs | **Monitoring → Application Insights** → then open the Insights resource (“View Application Insights data” if shown) → Transaction search / Logs |
| Raw app logs stream | **Monitoring → Log stream** or **App Service logs** |
| Kusto / workspace queries on the app | **Monitoring → Logs** (App Service Logs blade — different from Application Insights until linked) |

### How to phrase directions to Chris

1. Open app **`stage-wf-worldpay-wrapper-api`**
2. Left menu → **Monitoring** → **Application Insights**
3. If prompted, open the linked Insights resource
4. Search for a known `transactionId` from Postman (e.g. last eCheck sale id) or `330` / `Invalid Payment Type`

For settings: **Settings → Environment variables** → filter/search by name → **Show value** (do not ask him to change Key Vault secrets).

